                                    <h6>
                                        <span>Section 6</span>Gap Analysis </h6>
                                </div>
                                <div class="typography-line">
                                    <p>
                                       The gap analysis, sometimes known as the IS failure, is assessed by analysis of two main components. One is the company, which is the user of information systems and the requirements and secondly, the IS user`s perception of the performance of the delivered system probably after using the system.  A difference in the expectation and the perception even in one transaction causes user dissatisfaction. The cause of dissatisfaction, in turn, results in the negative feeling of the user, forcing them to reject the system sometimes. Precisely, the system my mismatch the information with useful aspects or provide insufficient functionality. Moreover, the IS may provide poor performance and not fit the practices by the organization. Interestingly, the system may fail in all the mentioned fields but still conform to the purpose it is designed to perform and specific roles between the users and developers. Therefore, the information systems must be crossed from one side of the organization as a bridge between the technological solutions and organizational problems. Regardless of the values of a system project, it may not perform as expected by the users causing the gap.
